*New Study Outlines How to Reconcile Trade and Climate Change Goals
*Cancun, Mexico, 8 December 2010 -- A new study launched today at the 
United Nations Climate Change Conference (COP16), From Collision to 
Vision: Climate Change and World Trade, will form an integral part of 
today's symposium organized by the International Centre for Trade and 
Sustainable Development in Cancún, Mexico. In the study, the Working 
Group on Trade and Climate Change outlines how a clash between trade and 
climate change can be avoided and suggests how the World Trade 
Organization (WTO) can advance trade while achieving climate change goals.
See: http://www.weforum.org/en/media/Latest%20News%20Releases/
