                    <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3"><b>New
                        Study Outlines How to Reconcile Trade and
                        Climate Change Goals<br>
                      </b>Cancun, Mexico, 8 December 2010 &#8211; A new study
                      launched today at the United Nations Climate
                      Change Conference (COP16), From Collision to
                      Vision: Climate Change and World Trade, will form
                      an integral part of today&#8217;s symposium organized by
                      the International Centre for Trade and Sustainable
                      Development in Canc&uacute;n, Mexico. In the study, the
                      Working Group on Trade and Climate Change outlines
                      how a clash between trade and climate change can
                      be avoided and suggests how the World Trade
                      Organization (WTO) can advance trade while
                      achieving climate change goals.<br>
                      See: <a
href="http://www.weforum.org/en/media/Latest%20News%20Releases/NR_Trade_Climate_2010">http://www.weforum.org/en/media/Latest%20News%20Releases/<br>
                        NR_Trade_Climate_2010</a><br>
                      <br>
